this morning

26:29.462 --> 26:31.381
- 'cause he's too much of a distraction.
- How did that go?

26:31.548 --> 26:32.799
- Pretty good.
- Pretty good, huh?

26:32.924 --> 26:36.344
You need to change the flow rate,
that's why your experiment's not working.

26:37.220 --> 26:39.431
- Wait, what?
- You need to change the flow rate.

26:41.141 --> 26:42.809
How do you know
what we're working on here?

26:44.269 --> 26:46.229
Because my TA Rakesh let me
look at his notes.

26:46.354 --> 26:48.148
He's a Cubs fan, I bought him a hat.

26:50.609 --> 26:51.568
Come on.

27:19.512 --> 27:20.764
CHANNING:
It's over here.

27:22.098 --> 27:24.684
Where are we on the flow rate?

27:24.893 --> 27:27.145
- What's up, dude?
- Hey, what's up?

27:27.854 --> 27:30.815
It's not the flow rate, I tried that.
We think maybe changing

27:30.899 --> 27:32.525
the viscosity a little bit might...

27:32.692 --> 27:34.402
You... Um, you...

27:34.819 --> 27:38.531
you did, you sped up
the flow rate but in order to...

27:38.657 --> 27:42.577
to... to maintain the average
linear velocity you... you need

27:42.702 --> 27:45.747
to also increase the dimension
of the five outlet channels.

27:50.043 --> 27:52.295
- That's not true. I personally tried...
- Yes, it is.

27:59.177 --> 28:00.220
Yes, it is.

28:02.430 --> 28:03.348
Mm-hmm.

28:04.182 --> 28:05.558
She's one of my freshmen.

28:06.810 --> 28:08.061
Fuck, you're a freshman.

28:10.855 --> 28:11.981
You're in.

28:14.109 --> 28:16.027
- Could you get her lab coat?
- Nice.

28:22.575 --> 28:24.577
Channing said he would hear my ideas
for products

28:24.661 --> 28:26.454
and we're working on such
amazing technology.

28:26.538 --> 28:28.373
<i>That professor is in love with you.</i>

28:28.540 --> 28:29.999
No, he's not!

28:30.500 --> 28:33.545
Whatever.
Am I going to see you this summer?

28:34.879 --> 28:37.757
- See me?
- Yeah. See you.

28:40.093 --> 28:41.177
Uh...

28:41.761 --> 28:43.555
I don't know. What are you up to?

28:44.973 --> 28:45.974
I'm very busy.

28:46.975 --> 28:49.269
I'm going to be driving
around in my new Lamborghini.

28:49.728 --> 28:52.063
<i>Oh, you got a Lamborghini?</i>

28:52.564 --> 28:55.483
-<i>Yes, the most expensive one.</i>
- Why?

28:55.984 --> 28:57.736
<i>Because I can.</i>

28:59.195 --> 29:01.072
Because no one thinks
that you're a terrorist

29:01.239 --> 29:02.532
when you drive a Lamborghini.

29:02.866 --> 29:04.784
<i>- Motherfuckers.</i>

29:06.828 --> 29:08.329
CHANNING:
<i>So, you wrote this up this summer?</i>

29:08.705 --> 29:11.583
Yeah, I had a little too much downtime
at my internship.

29:11.750 --> 29:13.376
So, it's a... it's a patch.

29:14.461 --> 29:15.587
I see that.

29:16.045 --> 29:19.674
It's a wearable device
that administers a drug,

29:19.883 --> 29:20.967
just like an antibiotic...

29:21.176 --> 29:23.052
directly into the patient's bloodstream

29:23.303 --> 29:25.180
while simultaneously monitoring

29:25.346 --> 29:26.931
whether the medication is working.

29:27.640 --> 29:31.644
It's diagnosis and therapy
at the same time.

29:31.936 --> 29:33.688
Huh. Yeah.

29:34.689 --> 29:35.857
I wanna start a company,

29:37.192 --> 29:38.777
and I'd like you to be a founding member.

29:39.152 --> 29:41.237
- I don't wanna wait.

29:41.946 --> 29:43.364
David Filo and Jerry Yang

29:43.531 --> 29:47.243
started Yahoo while they were
in your program, you must have invested.

29:48.244 --> 29:50.205
Actually, they asked me and I said, "No."

29:51.247 --> 29:52.582
I wish I could take that one back.

29:55.543 --> 29:58.004
You know what? I'm gonna put you
in touch with a physician,

29:58.671 --> 30:02.383
talk about the viability of this.
Do you know... Phyllis Gardner?

30:19.317 --> 30:20.777
Channing Robertson sent you?

30:21.069 --> 30:23.029
Yes, I'm in his graduate research group

30:23.571 --> 30:25.240
as a... a sophomore.

30:27.575 --> 30:29.702
Um... It's never gonna work.

30:29.911 --> 30:32.914
A patch is too small to store full doses

30:33.122 --> 30:35.208
of a single drug,
let alone multiple drugs

30:35.416 --> 30:37.544
and the reagents needed
for long-term testing.

30:37.710 --> 30:41.256
But then even if it could,
it would have to provide long-term storage

30:41.756 --> 30:44.551
for those chemicals at body temperature.

30:44.634 --> 30:47.178
And let's just...
l... let's put all that aside.

30:47.512 --> 30:51.182
Let's... let's say that you were able
to work out a way to do any of that.

30:52.100 --> 30:54.853
If you think that people want a patch

30:55.436 --> 30:56.938
to diagnose them

30:57.105 --> 31:00.358
and then put medicine directly
into their skin,

31:00.775 --> 31:03.319
then you've never met
a sick person before.

31:04.571 --> 31:08.992
People go to school for a very long time
to understand how to diagnose patients.

31:09.325 --> 31:10.869
You can't get a diagnosis
from a patch

31:11.035 --> 31:12.787
because human beings aren't machines.

31:13.162 --> 31:15.081
But doctors make mistakes.

31:15.874 --> 31:18.167
And this would be
based on data, so...

31:18.293 --> 31:20.086
Well, data isn't everything.

31:20.378 --> 31:22.422
Um, people your age
need to remember

31:22.589 --> 31:26.342
that machines make mistakes too,
especially when humans are operating them.

31:26.759 --> 31:28.511
- Yeah, but...
- It's... it's fine.

31:28.720 --> 31:30.346
It's, uh, nothing personal.

31:30.513 --> 31:32.265
You had an idea.
It's not gonna work,

31:32.390 --> 31:34.475
so you just... you keep learning.

31:34.726 --> 31:35.685
Keep trying.

31:37.145 --> 31:40.732
I'm gonna be heading home
and very nice to meet you.

31:43.943 --> 31:46.738
"Do or do not. There is no try."

31:47.280 --> 31:48.156
What?

31:49.032 --> 31:51.492
That's Yoda from <i>Star Wars.</i>

31:53.077 --> 31:53.953
Oh.

31:59.500 --> 32:00.668
Professor Gardner!

32:01.961 --> 32:02.921
Wait, wait!

32:03.338 --> 32:06.341
I just think that...
I think that we can work together.

32:07.508 --> 32:08.635
- Work together?
- Yeah.

32:08.801 --> 32:10.803
You're... you're a... what?
Freshmen, sophomore?

32:11.054 --> 32:13.890
- I just started my sophomore year.
- So you've had a couple of classes,

32:13.973 --> 32:16.351
maybe a seminar or two,
and now you think you know enough

32:16.476 --> 32:17.477
to start a company?

32:18.519 --> 32:20.229
I just thought as... as a woman,
you...

32:20.396 --> 32:22.732
Well, as a woman,
let me explain something to you.

32:22.857 --> 32:25.109
You don't get to skip any steps.

32:25.944 --> 32:27.487
You have to do the work.

32:27.904 --> 32:31.407
Your work, other people's work.
You have to do so much work,

32:31.574 --> 32:33.785
that they have to admit that you did it.
Nobody helped you.

32:33.868 --> 32:37.622
You have to take away all their excuses.
And then if you get anything,

32:37.956 --> 32:41.376
anything wrong, they'll destroy you,
and they'll be so happy to do it,

32:41.542 --> 32:43.419
so no, as a woman,
I can't help you right now.

32:44.045 --> 32:45.088
And just...

32:45.755 --> 32:46.756
...one other thing.

32:46.923 --> 32:52.804
Don't ever quote Yoda
to anybody ever again. Science is trying.

32:53.638 --> 32:54.889
That's all that it is.

32:55.473 --> 32:57.433
You only get to really do something

32:57.558 --> 32:59.644
when you've been trying for so long
that doing

32:59.727 --> 33:02.855
doesn't even seem possible anymore.
So, science is real.

33:02.939 --> 33:06.985
Yoda is a fictional green character
who apparently knows everything

33:07.110 --> 33:11.280
in the universe, except for syntax
and grammar.

33:11.406 --> 33:14.951
So, I'm sorry, your idea's impossible,
but that's the way the world works.

33:15.201 --> 33:19.914
The world works in certain ways
until a great idea comes along

33:20.123 --> 33:22.166
and... and changes everything.

33:22.458 --> 33:24.752
Okay, I'm gonna...
I'm gonna go, now.

33:24.919 --> 33:27.380
My husband is waiting for me
with a glass of red wine

33:27.547 --> 33:31.217
and a foot massage, and the DVD
of <i>My Big Fat Greek Wedding</i>

33:31.300 --> 33:35.096
which came in the mail today,
so I suggest you find a version

33:35.179 --> 33:36.973
of that for yourself.

33:37.098 --> 33:38.433
You're 19.

33:39.225 --> 33:41.519
You don't have to be anything else
right now.

33:58.494 --> 33:59.746
Bee-bo-bee-bo-beep.

34:00.955 --> 34:03.291
What do we have here?

34:04.584 --> 34:07.545
Oh. Oh, wow, that's alive. Yep.

34:09.756 --> 34:12.175
You are gonna come up with a new thing.

34:14.135 --> 34:15.720
Should I just stop? What should I do?

34:16.888 --> 34:20.224
Well, you could, I don't know,
like,

34:20.892 --> 34:23.352
try being a sophomore
in college for a night.

34:23.811 --> 34:24.771
That might be fun.

34:25.438 --> 34:26.564
You like acapella?

34:27.607 --> 34:30.735
You ever heard "Don't Stop Believin'"
in a 12-part harmony?

34:32.028 --> 34:33.112
It's fun.

34:41.996 --> 34:43.081
That's so funny!

34:47.668 --> 34:48.669
Hey!

34:51.589 --> 34:52.757
How are you guys?

34:53.758 --> 34:56.344
Oh, my God, that's hilarious.
Oh...

34:57.178 --> 34:58.805
Oh, my God, that's hilarious.

34:59.680 --> 35:01.057
That's the best joke ever.

35:01.349 --> 35:04.143
That's so funny. I'm having so much fun!

35:04.268 --> 35:05.353
Whoo-hoo.

35:05.645 --> 35:07.146
Whoo-hoo!

35:07.688 --> 35:08.856
Whoo-hoo!

35:09.357 --> 35:10.608
Whoo!

35:18.950 --> 35:21.035
<i>Ms. Holmes? Ms. Holmes?</i>

35:21.410 --> 35:22.745
Please answer the question.

35:23.121 --> 35:24.163
I...

35:25.164 --> 35:26.749
don't remember specifically.

35:27.750 --> 35:28.960
You were the CEO.

35:29.836 --> 35:30.795
Yes.

35:31.671 --> 35:33.339
<i>And you don't</i>
<i>remember specifically?</i>

35:33.422 --> 35:34.841
ELIZABETH:<i> I... I don't... um...</i>

35:36.175 --> 35:38.678
<i>no, I don't recall details from years ago.</i>

35:38.803 --> 35:40.054
<i>I... I... I...</i>

35:41.013 --> 35:42.056
<i>I don't recall...</i>

35:56.988 --> 35:58.364
MALE VOICE:<i> Ms. Holmes.</i>

36:01.909 --> 36:05.204
- Ms. Holmes, do you need a break?
- No.

36:10.793 --> 36:13.337
What's wrong with her?
Did something happen?

36:13.921 --> 36:17.049
At the party, I think a guy
did something to her.

36:17.341 --> 36:19.969
I don't know the whole story,
but she went to the police.

36:20.261 --> 36:22.763
- The police?
-She said it was rape.

36:22.972 --> 36:24.098
Really?

36:25.057 --> 36:26.142
Do you believe her?

36:26.517 --> 36:28.686
- I don't know. Let's go.

36:47.246 --> 36:48.247
Hello.

36:48.372 --> 36:49.999
<i>Hey, where have you been?</i>

36:50.166 --> 36:51.918
<i>I tried calling you for a few days.</i>

36:52.293 --> 36:53.377
I've been busy.

36:53.836 --> 36:57.173
I miss you. You know how much
I miss you when I don't talk to you.

36:57.840 --> 37:00.635
<i>Do you know how weird that is</i>
<i>that you would say that to me?</i>

37:01.761 --> 37:02.845
<i>I'm 19.</i>

37:04.847 --> 37:06.098
I'm 19.

37:08.392 --> 37:11.020
You should talk
to somebody your own age.

37:11.938 --> 37:13.147
<i>That's what you want?</i>

37:15.691 --> 37:16.651
Yeah.

37:17.610 --> 37:18.486
Yes.

37:20.947 --> 37:22.240
This is fucking weird.

37:25.576 --> 37:26.911
Don't call me again.

37:58.109 --> 38:00.736
MALE VOICE:
Ms. Holmes. They're ready for you.

38:16.419 --> 38:17.753
What did they say?

38:18.337 --> 38:20.589
They aren't recommending
any disciplinary action.

38:20.715 --> 38:21.632
I know that.

38:22.800 --> 38:24.552
But what did they say?

38:26.012 --> 38:27.471
It's my word against his.

38:29.598 --> 38:30.891
They don't believe me.

38:33.602 --> 38:35.229
I can't get anyone to believe me.

38:44.655 --> 38:47.616
I c... I can't get this smell out.
I think we should just throw it out.

38:49.368 --> 38:53.247
Oh, my God! Th... this is dangerous.
This could hurt you!

38:53.456 --> 38:54.707
We should get rid of it.

38:57.710 --> 38:59.045
I need your help.

39:01.380 --> 39:02.381
Elizabeth.

39:03.299 --> 39:04.717
- Get under it.

39:05.009 --> 39:06.010
- Yeah. Come on.

39:06.260 --> 39:07.636
Oh, wait, wait, wait.

39:07.845 --> 39:09.013
Mom, I have to put it down,

39:09.096 --> 39:11.307
- I have to put it down. I have to.
- All right, all right.

39:11.474 --> 39:13.142
Slowly, slowly, slowly, slowly.
Okay.

39:15.644 --> 39:18.147
- I don't want to do this right now, I...
-Elizabeth.

39:18.314 --> 39:19.523
No, just go back to the hotel.

39:19.607 --> 39:21.525
- I... leave me alone, I'm...
- I believe you

39:23.611 --> 39:25.946
I believe you.
I believe everything you said.

39:33.621 --> 39:36.374
But I... I didn't... you told me
to be careful, and I didn't listen to you,

39:36.540 --> 39:37.541
I was drinking.

39:38.709 --> 39:41.253
Men will... take...

39:42.671 --> 39:45.633
and... take from you,

39:46.467 --> 39:49.512
so you have to decide right now

39:50.096 --> 39:52.973
if you are going to let that stop you.

39:55.184 --> 39:56.644
- But how will...
- You just put it away,

39:57.103 --> 39:58.813
and forget it.

39:59.688 --> 40:00.731
And...

40:03.109 --> 40:04.276
then one day...

40:05.694 --> 40:07.655
one day, you'll just be fine again....

40:11.909 --> 40:14.120
Come on. This thing smells awful.

40:16.705 --> 40:18.749
- Okay.
- Okay.

40:19.542 --> 40:22.002
- And one, two,

40:22.920 --> 40:23.796
three!

40:24.213 --> 40:25.673
Oh, God!

40:37.601 --> 40:38.894
I love you.

40:43.274 --> 40:44.733
We should wash our hands.

42:27.628 --> 42:28.504
You're back.

42:28.879 --> 42:29.922
I'm back.

42:30.714 --> 42:31.632
It's a redesign.

42:33.384 --> 42:35.302
It's a box the size of an iPod.

42:36.428 --> 42:39.515
And it doesn't administer medicine.
It tests your blood.

42:40.808 --> 42:42.309
<i>What if you could test your blood</i>

42:43.018 --> 42:44.144
in your own home?

42:46.063 --> 42:47.982
And what if it's not a whole vial,

42:49.233 --> 42:50.401
<i>but just a drop?</i>

42:51.277 --> 42:52.278
It would always be with you.

42:54.947 --> 42:57.491
And it... it could keep you safe.

43:43.120 --> 43:46.582
So, Channing wants us to begin
the research phase as soon as possible.

43:46.832 --> 43:48.792
We're renting office space
in East Palo Alto.

43:48.959 --> 43:51.962
But isn't that the part of the city
they told you not to go to

43:52.046 --> 43:53.964
- during orientation?
- Yeah, that's dangerous.

43:54.089 --> 43:56.175
- Yeah.
- I got lost there during the move in,

43:56.300 --> 43:58.552
when you sent me to...
the Urban Outfitters.

43:58.636 --> 44:01.347
We can't afford anything else right now.

44:02.139 --> 44:04.183
And I wanted to ask you if...

44:04.850 --> 44:06.018
you would consider...

44:06.852 --> 44:09.730
investing my tuition money
into the company.

44:11.565 --> 44:13.317
Well, how would we pay
for your tuition?

44:13.442 --> 44:17.112
Well, you won't have to, because I'm...
I'm going to drop out.

44:18.072 --> 44:19.990
- You're gonna do what?
- No. No!

44:20.366 --> 44:22.660
Steve Jobs dropped out.
Bill Gates dropped out.

44:22.951 --> 44:25.245
Michael Dell, Paul Allen.
Elon Musk...

44:25.329 --> 44:27.206
- Who's Paul Allen?
- He's the other Microsoft guy.

44:27.331 --> 44:29.541
I don't care.
You're not dropping out of Stanford.

44:29.667 --> 44:31.126
Start a company after you graduate.

44:31.251 --> 44:33.379
No, I... I don't even go
to class anymore anyway.

44:33.629 --> 44:34.797
Wait, you don't go to class?

44:36.548 --> 44:38.634
Elizabeth, is this about
what happened?

44:38.759 --> 44:41.011
- Noel.
- No. No.

44:53.482 --> 44:55.776
What does this thing even do?
It...

44:57.152 --> 44:58.195
tests your blood?

44:58.362 --> 45:00.406
It's...

45:01.365 --> 45:04.535
Mom, you would never have
to have a needle ever again.

45:17.464 --> 45:18.924
I don't understand you.

45:21.552 --> 45:22.761
I know.

45:26.515 --> 45:29.893
Guess what?
Elizabeth Holmes dropped out of Stanford.

45:30.060 --> 45:32.604
And get this,
she invented a medical device,

45:32.813 --> 45:34.189
some sort of blood testing thing.

45:34.690 --> 45:36.650
A professor from Stanford
is helping her.

45:36.775 --> 45:38.402
They already raised a lot of money.

45:38.902 --> 45:41.029
- She didn't call for my advice.
- What do you mean?

45:41.572 --> 45:44.950
She's going to be doing
the exact same thing that I'm doing.

45:45.492 --> 45:46.785
She doesn't call me?

45:47.161 --> 45:50.122
She's a kid. She probably doesn't have
our phone number.

45:50.914 --> 45:51.999
No.

45:53.709 --> 45:56.962
'Cause they all think
they're better than us. That whole family.

45:57.713 --> 46:02.009
- Anyway, Mrs. Holmes said that...
- Why do you call her Mrs. Holmes?

46:02.092 --> 46:03.343
She calls you Lorraine.

46:04.386 --> 46:06.138
Why do you call her Mrs. Holmes?

46:06.805 --> 46:08.265
I never thought about it.

46:19.651 --> 46:23.030
- She should have called me.
- Don't make a big thing of it.

46:23.864 --> 46:25.032
I'm not.

46:27.326 --> 46:29.369
I just think
she should have called me.

47:11.203 --> 47:12.204
What happened?

47:13.914 --> 47:15.249
Was someone shooting at you?

47:16.208 --> 47:17.125
No.

47:17.876 --> 47:19.044
It was a stray bullet.

47:19.878 --> 47:21.338
There was a fight, I think.

47:23.507 --> 47:24.591
Thank you for coming.

47:29.012 --> 47:30.430
Why did you call me?

47:31.557 --> 47:33.225
You told me never to talk to you again.

47:39.147 --> 47:40.274
I don't know.

47:40.941 --> 47:42.734
Yes, you do! Why am I here?

47:45.237 --> 47:46.697
Why am I here?

48:01.795 --> 48:03.964
You can't push me away again.

48:06.300 --> 48:07.759
I'm going to protect you.

48:15.976 --> 48:18.270
I know. I know.

48:18.520 --> 48:20.188
<i>MALE VOICE:</i>
<i>Do you ever recall telling anyone,</i>

48:20.272 --> 48:22.399
<i>your patients, your investors, your board,</i>

48:22.983 --> 48:24.484
<i>that in fact none of the technology</i>

48:24.568 --> 48:26.403
<i>you claimed to have invented</i>
<i>was operational?</i>

48:27.279 --> 48:29.698
<i>And that the results they received</i>
<i>were often inaccurate?</i>

48:30.657 --> 48:32.784
<i>Do you recall telling any of these people</i>
<i>that your company</i>

48:32.868 --> 48:35.454
<i>was endangering their lives</i>
<i>by giving them false information</i>

48:35.537 --> 48:36.622
<i>about their health?</i>

48:40.751 --> 48:42.002
I knew that we made...

48:43.337 --> 48:44.713
so many mistakes,

48:44.838 --> 48:46.256
but we were...

48:47.174 --> 48:48.050
we were trying to...

48:48.175 --> 48:51.553
to take this forward,
and at that time,

48:52.387 --> 48:53.263
we thought

48:53.805 --> 48:55.349
that we were doing the right thing.
